<TEXT>
president bush the latest in a long line of 
leaders to declare war against drugs is tackling a 100 
billionayear narcotics industry with a 79 billion program 
already embroiled in political dispute 
bush describes the program he announced in his first nationally 
televised address as a plan that is as comprehensive as the 
problem 
to critics such as rep charles rangel dny chairman of the 
house select committee on narcotics it is a thousand points of 
light with no batteries 
quite frankly said senate judiciary committee chairman 
joseph biden the presidents plan is not tough enough bold 
enough or imaginative enough to meet the crisis at hand 
quite simply congressional democrats are not willing to let bush 
