biden for example is already calling for higher taxes on wine 
beer and cigarettes to finance the drug war 
bush however insists that the battle can be waged without 
raising taxes or increasing the deficit he proposed siphoning more 
than 751 million from other areas including juvenile justice 
housing immigration and economic development 
politicians of every stripe recognize that americans are anxious 
for action a gallup poll released at the white house last month 
found that a record 27 percent of adults view drugs as the most 
important problem facing the nation more serious than poverty the 
economy the environment and even fear of war that survey was taken 
even before the declaration of war by drug barons against the 
government of colombia 
despite efforts by every president for decades the drug problem 
in america has swollen to immense proportions with cocaine more 
plentiful purer cheaper and more in demand than ever 
its big business for drug lords in latin america and their us 
lieutenants the us chamber of commerce estimates illegal drug 
sales at 110 billion annually more than double the profits of all 
the fortune 500 companies combined 
there are plenty of willing consumers about 21 million americans 
have tried cocaine 3 million still use it occasionally and 1 
million report being heavy users 
