<TEXT>
president bush has called for better 
coordination and advanced technology to stop the flow of cocaine 
but a new military headquarters on the battlefront shows the 
limitations of the armed forces 
joint task force 4 in key west is intended to coordinate 
information not only from all branches of the military but from the 
customs service the coast guard the drug enforcement 
administration and other civilian agencies 
but the center was forced upon a reluctant military by congress 
which designated the defense department as the lead agency for drug 
intelligence and backed that up with 450 million this year 
much of that information is to come from an array of equipment 
including radar balloons flying up to 15000 feet awacs planes with 
a radar radius of 250 miles or more other aircraft bristling with 
infrared cameras hydrofoils so fast their speed is classified and 
presumably satellite reconnaissance 
the centers secondincommand rear adm john pearson refuses 
to confirm whether the center uses satellites even though jtf4 has 
a satellite in its unit emblem 
the idea is for all agencies to forward data to jtf4 which then 
will monitor suspected smuggling boats and planes 
pearson said the center which began operations in the spring 
can track virtually every plane and boat that crosses the caribbean 
a similar center in alameda calif covers the west coast 
id be crazy to say an airplane literally cant fly into this 
country without being seen but i can offer that there would be 
damned few that werent seen the admiral said 
but beyond tracking what jtf4 must do is sort innocent 
traffic from suspicious targets then find someone in a position to 
board the boat or force down the plane 
resources to do that are meager as illustrated by the 
frustrations of an aerostat radar balloon ship operating out of key 
west said coast guard lt ronald kochan who heads that operation 
the ships balloon has an effective radar range of a little less 
than 60 miles and is usually stationed at ocean choke points 
through which seaborne drug boats must travel 
working with one cutter we might detect 37 targets a day and 
on an average maybe two are boarded he said wed have to bring 
the whole east coast coast guard down here to give us 10 cutters to 
work with 
the more sophisticated drug traffickers know the ships schedule 
anyway he said 
although jtf4 touts the coast guard balloons as one of the key 
sources for its radar data kochan told a dismayed group of visiting 
congressmen that no electronic connection exists between the ship 
and the new center 
he added that no plan existed to make such a connection and that 
there was no equipment for it and no budget to buy the necessary 
equipment in any case 
but the biggest question hanging over the center is whether its 
mission is even necessary 
with much fanfare the coast guard and customs have set up their 
