clifford e vargas who transformed a boys 
dream of the oldtime circus into a revival of the traditional 
threering big top has died he was 64 
vargas died monday night of heart disease at his hollywood hills 
home according to a press release from his circus vargas 
the grandson of portuguese circus owners vargas grew up on a 
farm in pleasanton 
he held a variety of jobs including fuller brush salesman and 
chicago nightclub owner before going to work as a promoter for a 
circus which he eventually bought from the owner 
later he founded circus vargas with three trucks and eight 
animals in the early years he served as ticket taker ringmaster 
and truck driver 
the circus which celebrated its 20th anniversary this year grew 
to include 150 animals and up to 300 employees it is billed as the 
largest traveling tented circus in the worldup to 3 million people 
attend the circus each year in shows held in more than 100 us and 
canadian cities 
vargas is survived by three brothers and a sisterinlaw funeral 
arrangements were pending 
