<TEXT>
hurricane gabrielle churned toward bermuda and the 
east coast with winds of 135 mph today raising 10foot swells up to 
1300 miles away on north carolinas outer banks 
gabrielles 500mile wide spiral bypassed the caribbean and was 
expected to reach bermuda by friday or saturday the island got 
15foot swells today 
already the atlantic seasons biggest hurricane it was upgraded 
tuesday evening to a category 4 hurricane with 5 the strongest 
an air force reconnaissance plane flew over gabrielle late 
tuesday and reported rising barometric pressure and a slightly 
expanding eye in the hurricane signs that strengthening could be 
unlikely forecasters said 
but early today gabrielles pressure decreased slightly and its 
eye constricted again 
as of noon gabrielle was centered near 24 north latitude and 59 
west longitude 610 miles southsoutheast of bermuda it was moving 
northnorthwest at 12 mph and was expected to take a more northerly 
course in the next 24 hours 
early today a buoy on the outer banks recorded 10foot swells 
from the distant hurricane said hurricane specialist jim gross 
while it was uncertain how close gabrielle would come to bermuda 
its considerable size prompted forecasters to advise residents of 
the island and the east coast to monitor it closely 
forecasters said the storm rivaled last years recordsetting 
hurricane gilbert at the same stage but was on a path more like 
1985s powerful hurricane gloria which did 900 million in damage 
as it raced up the east coast 
gilberts winds reached more than 155 mph and had the lowest 
central pressure measured this century at 888 millibars central 
pressure governs wind intensity gilbert was ranked category 5 
gabrielles pressure increased from 942 millibars to 945 millibars 
late tuesday 
while gilbert stayed on a westerly course across the upper 
caribbean devastating jamaica and landing in mexico gabrielle 
dodged past the caribbean and headed up into the atlantic 
gloria roared up the atlantic in the fall of 1985 at an unusually 
fast 30 to 50 mph panicking thousands of east coast residents but 
its winds dropped from 150 mph to minimal hurricane strength by the 
time it reached land 
in barbados the easternmost caribbean island 550 miles southeast 
of puerto rico gabrielles tail caused 10foot waves and some 
flooding in beachfront homes and businesses in the capital of 
bridgetown no injuries or serious damage were reported 
