police in five towns wednesday during demonstrations demanding the 
resignation of president roh taewoo and the withdrawal of us 
troops from south korea 
police fired tear gas to break up the rallies in masan seoul 
pusan suwon and taegu witnesses reported some arrests and injuries 
but police had no figures 
in the southern industrial city of masan 205 miles south of 
