<TEXT>
here is a brief chronology of us 
involvement in lebanon 
july 15 1958 president dwight eisenhower sends us marines to 
beirut at the request of christian president camille chamoun to 
quell an uprising by chamouns rivals however the marines never 
took part in any fighting and they were quietly withdrawn soon 
afterward 
aug 25 1982 following israels june 1982 invasion 800 us 
marines part of a 5400man peacekeeping force with british french 
and italian units go ashore to oversee the evacuation of israeli 
syrian and plo forces from beirut the us force was later 
increased to 1800 men 
april 19 1983 a shiite moslem suicide bomber rams an 
explosivespacked van into the seaside us embassy in west beirut 
killing 63 people including 17 americans 
oct 23 1983 a shiite suicide bomber attacks the us marine 
base near beirut airport killing 241 men another suicide bomber 
hits a french paratroopers base killing 58 men 
dec 5 1983 us navy fighterbombers attack syrian missile and 
artillery batteries in lebanon inflicting significant damage 
after reconnaissance planes are fired on 
dec 14 1983 the battleship uss new jersey bombards moslem 
positions with 250 shells from its 16inch guns as the situation 
deteriorates 
feb 26 1984 as lebanons civil war breaks out again the 
marines are pulled back to us warships off beirut beginning the 
final withdrawal after an illfated 22month peacekeping operation 
in which 264 us servicemen were killed 
sept 20 1984 suicide bomber hits us embassy annex in north 
beirut killing 12 people and wounding 96 including the us 
ambassador 
march 16 1985 four armed kidnappers drag terry anderson the 
chief middle east correspondent of the associated press from his 
car in beirut he is the longest held of 16 foreign hostages in 
lebanon eight of them americans 
sept 6 1989 staff of us embassy evacuates after hundreds of 
christian protesters besiege the facility to demand that the united 
states help the christians in their 6monthold battle with syrian 
forces 
</TEXT>
