initial period of discussion has been beneficial 
the executives said talks so far have concentrated on exploring 
a combination that would add value to client service capitalize on 
shared values of commitment to quality and provide enhanced 
opportunities to personnel of both firms 
andersen spokesman jack ruane and price waterhouse spokeswoman 
deborah rothschild both said they could not comment further because 
the firms had agreed to keep details of the discussions confidential 
some potential obstacles to a merger include how to reconcile the 
firms compensation and retirement systems and foreign operations 
as well as how to handle merging andersens very successful 
