<TEXT>
tokyo isnt necessarily the worlds most expensive 
city when its prices of cameras videocassette recorders and some 
other items are compared with those in new york a government agency 
said wednesday 
the ministry of international trade and industry said its report 
was based on a survey conducted in late august of prices of eight 
consumer products also including video cameras and compact 
diskradio cassette players 
japan excels in producing light compact cameras and video 
equipment and exports them to the united states and elsewhere while 
importing few such products itself 
the ministry said at an exchange rate of 144 yen to the dollar 
cameras and video equipment sold at discount shops in new york cost 
more than those sold in discount stores in tokyo 
the report said prices of five models of cameras sold in new york 
were an average 14 percent higher than in tokyo 
it said new york prices were 45 percent higher for vcrs and 34 
percent higher for compact disk players 
a camera with a zoom lens and case cost 96900 yen 673 at a 
discount shop in tokyo against 113750 yen 790 in new york a vcr 
cost 78000 yen 542 in tokyo against 117200 yen 814 in new 
york the report said 
ministry officials said results of the survey were shown to the 
us delegation during justended bilateral trade talks us 
participants in the talks repeatedly said that identical products 
made in japan were more expensive here than overseas 
according to a survey of more than 100 cities by business 
international a genevabased research and consulting company tokyo 
was the worlds most expensive city and had a costofliving index 
of 203 taking new york as the base of 100 in 1987 
in 1988 the survey said inflation and shortages of goods made 
tehran the worlds most expensive city ending tokyos fouryear run 
at the top of the list tehran had an index of 209 followed by 
tokyo at 202 
