growing checkprinting business and enhance its ability to take 
advantage of new opportunities that develop with the deregulation of 
us interstate banking the company said 
mb america has agreed to buy american bank stationery from an 
investment group that includes company management and headed by the 
new york investment banking firm gibbons green van amerongen 
gibbons green specialists in management buyouts had led the 
investment group in acquiring american bank stationery from american 
standard inc in 1986 for about 995 million 
american bank stationery based in baltimore is the third 
largest us check printer it has about 2300 employees working at 
29 imprint plants and 2 base printing plants in 21 states 
mb america said the acquisition will complement its existing 
checkprinting operations it already owns clarke checks inc based 
in san antonio texas which is the fourth biggest company in the 
business 
