officials of midway and ampcopittsburgh had not discussed ampcos 
interest in the chicagobased airline the nations 16th largest 
were treating it as a routine business investment she said 
midway chairman david hinson has said midway is not interested in 
being acquired 
ampco said its subsidiary ampcopittsburgh securities ii corp 
acquired 960000 shares of midway common stock as of sept 5 at an 
average price of 1677 a share midway closed at 2062 a share 
wednesday on the new york stock exchange up 162 
midway announced last week it had strengthened its defenses 
against a hostile takeover by loosening the trigger on its 
shareholder rights plan commonly called a poison pill 
the shareholder rights plan would take effect if an outsider 
acquired 15 percent of midways stock the plan would increase the 
number of outstanding shares to make a buyout prohibitively 
expensive 
midway founded in 1979 is a fastgrowing airline serving 51 
us cities from los angeles to boston and from chicago to miami it 
operates from midway airport in chicago 
ampcopittsburgh owns buffalo forge co and union electric steel 
corp 
