<TEXT>
banca nazionale del lavoro has filed a complaint with 
italian justice officials against the former manager of its branch 
in atlanta ga over alleged unauthorized transactions the bank 
announced wednesday 
banca nazionale italys largest stateowned bank is under 
investigation by us and italian authorities for alleged 
irregularities at the atlanta branch in the financing of exports to 
iraq 
banca nazionale said last week that the matter involved 2500 
transactions by its atlanta branch that were not authorized by 
either the banks north american management or the head office in 
rome 
the transactions involved letters of credit for exports to iraq 
the exports concerned mostly grain and the bank has said no arms 
shipments were involved 
banca nazionale said the transactions were never reported on the 
books by the branch management it has not provided a reason for the 
alleged irregularities and said the value of the transactions has 
yet to be determined 
the bank has said the letters of credit while correct 
technically exceeded the credit ceiling that banca nazionale set 
for the branch the investigation was complicated by the 
sophisticated methods used to keep the transactions off the official 
books bank spokesman claudio cremona said 
the banks board of directors has announced an extraordinary 
meeting for thursday to discuss the atlanta affair many italian 
politicians have said banca nazionale chairman nerio nesi should 
step down 
banca nazionale said it suspended the atlanta branch manager 
christopher drogoul 35 and replaced him with luciano alfredo 
silvestri manager of its branch in miami fla 
banca nazionale is wholly owned by the italian treasury and by 
state entities but the bank has nonvoting savings shares trading 
on the milan stock exchange 
the seurities industry watchdog committee consob suspended 
trading in banca nazionale shares tuesday after they dropped 97 
percent to 14900 lire or 1050 monday down from 16500 lire or 
1180 friday and down from a 1989 high of 18210 lire or 13 
reached august 8 
the bank has said it doesnt expect to incur any losses from the 
affair because all transactions were guaranteed either by the us 
commodity credit corp or by the central bank of iraq 
banca nazionale has been under investigation by the us federal 
reserve system and georgia state banking authorities since the 
middle of august the bank of italy the central bank is 
collaborating in the probe 
